##Why Map fire alarm boxes and fire hydrants in Boston?

According to a recent (February 2020) Boston Globe article, Bostons fire alarm system was the first of its kind in the world, and received its first call 168 years ago. It was an electrical fire alarm telegraph system invented by Samuel F.B. Morse and Dr.William F. Channing. The system is still functional today with over 1800 boxes around the city of Boston and over 9000 calls received through the system - according to the Boston Globe. While we can all make calls using our phones, this system can still be handy - for example, during a network outtage. Out of curiousity, Ive mapped the fire alarm boxes relative to fire hydrants below.

Fire hydrants and alarm boxes in Boston
